1. How to add / remove events dynamically without using event attributes (eg:  onclick, ...)?

-->The addEventListener() method attaches an event handler to the specified element.
-->you can add many event handlers to one element
-->you can add many event handlers of the same type to one element, i.e two "click" events
--> you can add event listeners to any DOM
usage: refer sir examples.

--> The removeEventListener() method removes event handlers to the specified elements.
usage: refer sir examples.


2. How to destructuring arrays in JavaScript?

-->To destructure an array in Javascript, we use the square brackets[] to store the variable name which will be assigned to the name of the array storing the element.

--> const [var1, var2, .....] = arrayName;

